Tweet on Twitter













Fort Pitt Capital Group LLC decreased its stake in  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions (NASDAQ:USAP) by 3.six% through the first quarter, according to its most modern Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Fee (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 66,102 shares of the standard resources company’s stock right after providing two,five hundred shares through the period. Fort Pitt Capital Group LLC owned about .ninety two% of Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions worthy of $1,124,000 as of its most modern filing with the SEC. 
Quite a few other institutional traders also just lately purchased and offered shares of the enterprise. Royce & Associates LP raised its placement in  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions by 108.9% in the first quarter. Royce & Associates LP now owns 29,seven-hundred shares of the standard resources company’s stock valued at $505,000 right after purchasing an supplemental 15,480 shares through the last quarter.  Boston Partners raised its placement in  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions by 37.eight% in the first quarter. Boston Partners now owns one hundred fifteen,908 shares of the standard resources company’s stock valued at $1,970,000 right after purchasing an supplemental 31,800 shares through the last quarter.  Acadian Asset Management LLC raised its placement in  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions by fourteen.two% in the first quarter. Acadian Asset Management LLC now owns 31,513 shares of the standard resources company’s stock valued at $534,000 right after purchasing an supplemental 3,915 shares through the last quarter.  Thomson Horstmann & Bryant Inc. raised its placement in  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions by twelve.six% in the first quarter. Thomson Horstmann & Bryant Inc. now owns 320,350 shares of the standard resources company’s stock valued at $5,445,000 right after purchasing an supplemental 35,900 shares through the last quarter.  Last but not least, Renaissance Technologies LLC raised its placement in  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions by ten.% in the fourth quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 48,800 shares of the standard resources company’s stock valued at $659,000 right after purchasing an supplemental 4,433 shares through the last quarter. Institutional traders own  81.03% of the company’s stock. 

Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions (NASDAQ USAP) remained flat at $eighteen.00 through buying and selling on Wednesday. The stock experienced a buying and selling volume of two,304 shares. The firm’s 50 day transferring typical rate is $seventeen.seventy two and its two hundred-day transferring typical rate is $15.forty three. The stock’s current market capitalization is $129.ninety two million. Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions has a 1-12 months very low of $9.13 and a 1-12 months significant of $19.sixty seven. 
Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions (NASDAQ:USAP) last issued its quarterly earnings information on Friday, April twenty eighth. The standard resources enterprise claimed ($.11) earnings for every share (EPS) for the quarter, lacking the Zacks’ consensus estimate of ($.07) by $.04. Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions experienced a damaging return on equity of two.65% and a damaging net margin of 3.forty six%. The enterprise experienced revenue of $48.88 million for the quarter, in comparison to the consensus estimate of $forty two.24 million. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 23.4% in comparison to the exact same quarter last 12 months.  Analysts foresee that  Universal Stainless & Alloy Products and solutions will post $.twenty EPS for the existing fiscal 12 months. 
